<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910625-0025</DOCNO><DOCID>910625-0025.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Northrop Corp.:   Measures to Halt Takeovers   Are Adopted by Directors</HL><DATE>06/25/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10</SO><CO>   LABOR NOC</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><NS>LABOR, PERSONNEL ISSUES, TRENDS, MANAGEMENT TECHNIQUES (LAB)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Northrop Corp., Los Angeles, said its board adopted ananti-takeover measure to protect the surplus assets in itsretirement and pension plan.   The aerospace company would be limited for a period offive years after a change in control to using the surplusfunds to provide benefits to the plan's participants.Northrop said its pension and retirement plan assets areabout $1 billion more than projected liabilities.</LP><TEXT>   The board also adopted other anti-takeover measures,including prohibiting the payment of premiums on commonstock, known as &quot;greenmail,&quot; and reducing the threshold underwhich its existing shareholder rights plan would take effect.   Northrop said the actions weren't taken in response to anyacquisition attempt, and that it isn't aware of any effortsto acquire control of the company.</TEXT></DOC>